                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>visit down <placeName>South</placeName>, especially in\n                <placeName>Mobile</placeName><lb/> last spring, that I should much like<lb/> to\n                repeat it. You do not say a word about<lb/> our <placeName>Mobile</placeName>\n                friends nor have I heard a single<lb/> word from them since my return although<lb/>\n                I have written <persName>Dr. Wolff</persName> twice and have<lb/> sent several\n                verbal messages to him and<lb/> to his interesting family. I hope they<lb/> are in\n                good health and spirits, although<lb/> I can hardly expect the latter <add>?</add>\n                they<lb/> something more than humor. The<lb/> heathen Bloodhounds at\n                    <placeName>Washington</placeName><lb/> seem determined crush and beggar the<lb/>\n                entire <placeName>south</placeName> and her proper<add>?</add>. I earnestly<lb/>\n                pray that some power may yet frustrate<lb/> their informal plans.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Your monthly Parcels have been regularly<lb/> received and\n                distributed the Occident for<lb/> your <placeName>New York</placeName> subscribers\n                sent to me whilst<lb/> you <sic>was</sic> away I distributed though the P.O.<lb/>\n                Your last parcel by <persName>Adams &amp; Co</persName> was marked<lb/> paid by you,\n                but they insisted on collecting<lb/> the freight from me to the extent of 30Â¢</p>"
